    "short_description": {
        "value": "Galileo is a highly multimodal transformer model for remote sensing, capable of learning global and local features from diverse modalities (optical, SAR, elevation, weather, pseudo-labels, etc.) across space and time. It uses a dual self-supervised learning algorithm with global and local contrastive losses and is pretrained on a globally sampled, highly multimodal dataset. Galileo outperforms state-of-the-art specialist models on a wide range of remote sensing benchmarks.",
